- 'Gas separation' is a type of experiment where membranes are used to separate different gases;
- 'Performance metrics' include permeability and selectivity, which are crucial for evaluating the efficiency of membranes in gas separation processes.

- 'Performance metrics' include 'permeability' and 'selectivity';
- 'Solvent weight percentage' refers to the percentage of the solvent in the membrane;
